      • factorize

        public FactorizedBMatrix factorize(LinkNet matrix,
                          float[] bdiag,
                          float[] boffdiag,
                          int[] save)
        Create a factorized susceptance matrix using a LinkNet sparse symmetric model representation. Use this constructor to just run factorization a single time. To save the pattern and run multiple times with different B-values, use the other constructor. Neither the matrix nor susceptance arrays are modified
        Parameters:
        matrix - LinkNet sparse symmetric network.
        bdiag - diagonal susceptance values (array with size equal to number of buses)
        boffdiag - off-diagonal susceptance values (array with size equal to number of branches)
        Returns:
        factorized susceptance matrix

      • factorize

        public FactorizedBMatrix factorize(SpSymMtrxFactPattern pattern,
                          float[] bdiag,
                          float[] boffdiag)
        Create a factorized susceptance matrix using a saved pattern Neither the pattern nor susceptance arrays are modified
        Parameters:
        pattern - Existing factorizer
        bdiag - diagonal susceptance values (array with size equal to number of buses)
        boffdiag - off-diagonal susceptance values (array with size equal to number of branches)
        Returns:
        factorized susceptance matrix
